ZH: 在夏天，阳光会把整个房间都焐热了。
EN: In summer, the sun makes the entire room hot and stuffy.

ZH: 在寒冷的冬天，身体感觉需要不断的被暖气焐热。
EN: During the cold winter, our bodies crave to be warmed up by the heating system.

ZH: 这个炉子可以焐热一整个屋子。
EN: This stove can heat up an entire room.

ZH: 冰川中的冰块正在被火焐热，渐渐融化。
EN: The ice blocks in the glacier are being heated and slowly melting.

ZH: 炎炎夏日，阳光把沙滩上的沙子烤得焐热。
EN: On a scorching summer day, the sun bakes the sand on the beach, making it hot.

ZH: 在桑拿房里，热气把人的皮肤都焐热了。
EN: In a sauna, the steam heats up the skin.

ZH: 热带地区的太阳会焐热整个城市。
EN: The sun in tropical regions can heat up an entire city.

ZH: 在高温下，车内的空气被火烤得焐热。
EN: Under high temperatures, the air inside a car becomes hot.

ZH: 熨斗能将衣服烫平并焐热它们。
EN: The iron can flatten and heat up clothes.

ZH: 吃了一碗热腾腾的汤，身体感到焐热的舒适。
EN: After having a bowl of steaming hot soup, the body feels comfortably warmed.

ZH: 炉子的燃料燃烧后会产生火焰，把周围的空气焐热。
EN: The fuel burned in the stove produces flames that heat up the surrounding air.

ZH: 在干燥的沙漠里，炙热的太阳将整个环境都焐热起来。
EN: In the dry desert, the blazing sun heats up the entire environment.

ZH: 夏季的河水受到高温影响，变得焐热。
EN: The river water becomes hot during the summer due to high temperatures.

ZH: 当锅底变得焐热时，可以开始翻炒食材了。
EN: Once the bottom of the pan becomes hot, you can start stir-frying the ingredients.

ZH: 咖啡壶可以将水焐热，使咖啡变得浓郁可口。
EN: The coffee pot can heat up the water and make the coffee rich and delicious.

ZH: 房间里的电暖器可以将空气焐热，增加室内温度。
EN: The electric heater in the room can heat up the air and increase the indoor temperature.

ZH: 火焰的热量可以焐热锅底，使食物快速熟热。
EN: The heat from the flame can heat up the bottom of the pot, cooking the food quickly.

ZH: 在炎炎夏日，烈日将脸颊晒得焐热。
EN: In the scorching summer, the intense sun heats up the cheeks.

ZH: 在冷冻室里，食物会被花费一段时间焐热到解冻。
EN: In the freezer, it takes some time to heat up and thaw the food.

ZH: 炉子的火焰可以将室外的雪焐热，使其融化。
EN: The flames from the stove can heat up the snow outside, causing it to melt.
